Hi,

Frank, you&#39;ve been fair... more fair than I&#39;d be, in a similar situation.

I&#39;m not hearing anything new or interesting from the complainers and critics.  

I&#39;m here for conversations about... well, exactly what you said, &quot;what these voices are, and how to hear it and interpret it better.&quot;

Might some of this be pareidolia?  Of course.  We&#39;re not stupid... or at least most of us aren&#39;t.  Is ALL of it pareidolia?  Not a chance.

So let&#39;s get back to what&#39;s interesting: Searching for what the voices are, how to hear and interpret what they&#39;re saying, and which ones to take seriously.  Let&#39;s find ways to hear them so even the most adamant skeptic must concede that something interesting is going on here.  

(Of course, the very fact that they&#39;re still reading this list suggests that, in their heart of hearts, they do find the voices interesting, and deeply want to believe.)

Cheerfully,
Fiona


